One day, many moons ago, Jorge looked me dead in the eye on the precipice of an active volcano and said "Alex, come work for me and you will win honor, glory and an Emmy." Jorge did not lie, what an absolute trip!!! Beyond humbled and honored to win an Emmy for my work on Maya and the Three. Big thank thank you to @mexopolis and @tyoon80 for having me on this great show. It was an honor to contribute and be a part of such a wonderful team.
Still reeling from last night, I WON AN EMMY!!!!!!! Holy smokes, what an honor. Special thanks to @cathleenmcallister for being the perfect date on such a wonderful night.

SUPER ROBOT FIGHTER!! A book I made this year during the pandemic - a love letter to robots, to fighting games, to pop culture, to all things fighting tournaments, getting sloshed with your friends and watching some entertainment in the ring. Here's a small digital preview. Books still available in my store! Link in bio.

Blobbys Hab Unit. The first 'set' I designed for Dad while laying out the Cold Open with Yuhki. It was just the two of us in the art dpt at that time so we had to get our hands dirty. We wanted to lay it all out on the floor with the cold open intro and Blobbys apt was one of the things that helped introduce viewers to our 'lived in' world. Fincher, Ron Kobb, Otomo, Moebius, Tanaka, Shirow, I tried to throw it all in. So much stuff to post!!! #art #mydadthebountyhunter #netflix #visualdevelopment #artistsoninstagram #animationart #scifi #digitalpainting

Yuhki always said one of the first statements you can make in an animated show for your world is what do your vehicles look like? How pushed will you go? It becomes a good signifier for your shows shape language. I took that shit SERIOUS. The ubiquitious hover car of Dad became a one size fits all for our universe. The EHC opts for standardized templates of all hab units and vehicles to streamline their corporate stranglehold on the universe. Still to this day, I love this design a lot. #art #design #conceptdesign #visualdevelopment #mydadthebountyhunter

'I took a deep breath, steadying my hands as my heartbeat rattled my whole body. The tempo of my pulse shaking my limbs with a THUMP THUMP THUMP. I'd been left several disturbing voicemails over the course of three days. The first message I could distinguish, a familiar voice, the sound of birds in the background, the crackle of the satellite line. My brother had driven up to the cabin and had implored I come with him. As the messages went on I became increasingly worried until I decided to go find him. He was fervent, panicked even but recently that was nothing new so I ignored the signs. As I approached the door the sounds from those messages played through my head, multiple voices, the screaming, the shrill laughter, more voices, a language I couldn't place, more screaming. How many people was he with? What were they doing? I had to find out what was going on... I had to find my brother.' - From Hell of a Story.
